The '''Yggyn compromise''', also sometimes known as '''Yggyn's Choice''', was a negotiation tactic meant to overcome an impasse. If neither party could accept the proposal of the other, both chose to accept a third alternative, often arbitrarily made.

Such a compromise was made between [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] during the [[Corellian Crisis]]. Jade, being a trader at the time and familiar with the inner workings of the Empire, and Organa, the [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]] of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], were both familiar with the concept. They had fled [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] and had only one ship, the ''[[Jade's Fire]]'', but Leia wished to go to [[Drall (planet)|Drall]], and Mara wished to return secretly to Corellia. They chose to accept an Yggyn compromise and went instead to [[Selonia/Legends|Selonia]].

